  factsToSay:
  - CPR is performed at the rate of 100 - 120 beats per minute (bpm)
  - In CPR every 30 chest compressions, you should do 2 rescue breaths
  - 'CPR''s main purpose is to restore the partial flow of oxygenated blood to the
    brain and heart. '
  - CPR is used to delay tissue death and to extend the brief window for a successful
    resuscitation without permanent brain damage
  factInterval: 1
